Almost every website follows some type of grid structure.

00:00:05.160 --> 00:00:06.900
But where's the grid structure coming from?

00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:11.260
As it turns out, CSS allows us to control how wide our elements are and

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:12.790
how they're arranged on the page.

00:00:12.790 --> 00:00:14.760
But this should be a pretty easy task, right?

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:17.580
